Package com.twiceagain.selescript.interpreter.runtime

Class SSRuntimeContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twiceagain.selescript.interpreter.runtime.SSRuntimeContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class SSRuntimeContext
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Closeable
    The class that maintains the context of the current running program. There should be exactly one RuntimeContext per running script. It is created by providing the existing SSConfig object. It is directly responsible for managing loop and there associated timeouts/countout.
    Author:
    xavier
